WEBVTT

00:04.905 --> 00:07.206
[eerie theme music playing]

00:52.653 --> 00:54.219
[rattling chains]

01:01.962 --> 01:03.028
[straining]

01:05.966 --> 01:07.499
[struggling]

01:08.602 --> 01:10.803
[breathing heavily]

01:11.705 --> 01:14.039
[whimpers]

01:23.818 --> 01:27.619
[stifled screaming]

01:36.964 --> 01:39.131
[in distorted voice]
<i> Good afternoon,</i>
<i> my twisted friends.</i>

01:39.133 --> 01:41.500
<i> We have quite the show</i>
<i> for you today.</i>

01:41.602 --> 01:44.103
<i> Is it going to be</i>
<i> the fire of Ashes,</i>

01:44.105 --> 01:47.139
<i> or will it be</i>
<i> the chainsaw with Buzz?</i>

01:47.208 --> 01:51.643
<i> Or do you want to see</i>
<i> the magic of The Magician?</i>

01:55.216 --> 01:56.348
<i> There we are.</i>

01:56.417 --> 01:59.017
[chuckling] <i> Who's it</i>
<i> going to be?</i>

01:59.019 --> 02:00.519
<i> Who's it going to be?</i>

02:00.521 --> 02:01.720
<i> Come on, my darlings.</i>

02:01.855 --> 02:03.622
<i> If you want to have a say</i>
<i> in who gets to play,</i>

02:03.624 --> 02:05.724
<i> then get your tips in.</i>

02:05.859 --> 02:07.526
<i> Don't be so cheap.</i>

02:07.528 --> 02:09.328
<i> Majesty's watching.</i>

02:10.464 --> 02:12.664
<i> -Time's almost up, my friend</i>
-[struggling]

02:13.033 --> 02:15.300
<i> Five, four,</i>

02:15.302 --> 02:19.304
<i> -three, two, and one.</i>
-[straining]

02:19.306 --> 02:21.039
[stifled screams]

02:22.209 --> 02:23.508
<i> Great choice.</i>

02:23.511 --> 02:26.411
<i> If you like what you see,</i>
<i> leave Your Majesty a tip.</i>

02:33.053 --> 02:35.621
[panting]

02:38.459 --> 02:40.459
[distorted music playing]

02:40.561 --> 02:42.327
<i> ♪ Magician in the box ♪</i>

02:42.429 --> 02:44.329
<i> ♪ He likes to play all day ♪</i>

02:44.331 --> 02:46.064
<i> ♪ Magician in the box ♪</i>

02:46.133 --> 02:48.233
<i> ♪ He'd like to come today ♪</i>

02:48.302 --> 02:50.802
<i> ♪ Magician in the box ♪</i>

02:50.905 --> 02:52.804
<i> ♪ He wants to play today ♪</i>

02:52.907 --> 02:54.606
<i> ♪ Magician in the box ♪</i>

02:54.708 --> 02:56.608
<i> ♪ Oh what a dreamy day ♪</i>

02:56.610 --> 02:59.211
[struggling]

02:59.313 --> 03:01.713
[stifled screams]

03:04.118 --> 03:06.418
[shuddering]

03:10.424 --> 03:11.857
[man shouts]

03:11.959 --> 03:15.027
[muffled] No, no, no, no...

03:18.432 --> 03:21.099
[stifled screaming]

03:21.202 --> 03:22.701
[yelping]

03:22.803 --> 03:23.802
[muted]

03:23.937 --> 03:26.538
[gasping] Stop! Stop!
What is this?

03:26.607 --> 03:28.207
No, don't do it!

03:28.209 --> 03:30.509
[wailing] God, no!

03:30.611 --> 03:31.910
No! No!

03:31.912 --> 03:34.846
[struggling]

03:34.949 --> 03:37.816
[shrieking]

03:39.220 --> 03:41.820
[wailing]

03:41.955 --> 03:43.922
[screaming]

03:46.860 --> 03:48.160
[gagging]

04:12.519 --> 04:13.552
[in normal voice] It's over.

04:14.521 --> 04:15.721
Believable, right?

04:16.523 --> 04:18.657
[chuckles] I told you
I'd bring it.

04:19.326 --> 04:21.059
[sighs] Whew!

04:22.229 --> 04:23.428
[sighs]

04:23.430 --> 04:25.697
[shudders] Whoo!

04:25.699 --> 04:28.500
[sighs] Well,
that was a, uh...

04:29.470 --> 04:32.304
...a super freaky experience,
but, uh...

04:33.807 --> 04:35.507
...it was kinda
awesome. [chuckles]

04:36.343 --> 04:38.210
This is, this is clever.
Did you make this?

04:38.646 --> 04:39.511
Did you make this?

04:40.614 --> 04:41.613
Can I keep this?

04:41.615 --> 04:43.048
No.

04:43.117 --> 04:45.050
-[man] Oh.
-You were very convincing.

04:45.119 --> 04:47.219
But this is where
our arrangement ends.

04:47.221 --> 04:48.320
-Yeah, no, sure, no.
-[cocks gun]

04:48.322 --> 04:49.221
Hey, whoa...

04:49.356 --> 04:50.455
See, we know where you live,

04:50.524 --> 04:51.923
-Mr. 22 Brook Street.
-[man breathes heavily]

04:51.925 --> 04:52.958
We know where you work,

04:53.093 --> 04:54.726
and we know where
your kids go to school.

04:57.131 --> 04:58.230
Now disappear.

04:59.333 --> 05:01.433
-Understand?
-I understand.
I understand.

05:01.835 --> 05:02.901
That's a wrap.

05:42.710 --> 05:43.942
So, how'd we do?

05:45.412 --> 05:47.946
Mmm, numbers are still down.

05:50.017 --> 05:52.117
You know, I was thinking,
we should be brainstorming.

05:53.754 --> 05:56.855
We need to come up
with some new ideas,
new characters.

05:59.660 --> 06:00.759
What about...

06:02.162 --> 06:03.328
What about a clown?

06:04.965 --> 06:08.633
Uh, there's extra in here.

06:08.635 --> 06:11.603
-Just my way
of saying thank you.
-You don't...

06:13.107 --> 06:14.106
Thank you.

06:15.809 --> 06:17.709
Look, Max...

06:17.844 --> 06:19.845
There's not a lot of people
that can do what you do,

06:20.647 --> 06:22.948
and it's been working, but...

06:23.951 --> 06:26.251
Man, we gotta find a way
to make our audience grow.

06:26.954 --> 06:27.953
I got some ideas.

06:28.789 --> 06:30.455
Brainstorm while
I'm cleaning up.

06:31.725 --> 06:32.557
Do you want help?

06:32.659 --> 06:35.327
No. No. Go home.

06:39.333 --> 06:40.532
-[exhales]
-Okay.

06:44.304 --> 06:45.303
Night.

07:01.655 --> 07:03.755
-[dog whines softly]
-All right.

07:03.857 --> 07:05.524
Let's go make it safe.

07:17.304 --> 07:18.136
[dog cries]

07:53.707 --> 07:54.806
[barks]

07:54.875 --> 07:57.209
Shh, Hulky, I've gotta
get this right.

07:58.045 --> 07:59.044
[cries]

08:03.951 --> 08:04.816
Here we go.

08:14.628 --> 08:15.927
What do you think, Hulky?

08:16.630 --> 08:17.662
Should we cash some in?

08:22.836 --> 08:23.902
[whispers] Yeah.

08:24.705 --> 08:25.804
I'll just seal it.

08:37.951 --> 08:38.950
Can I help you?

08:39.052 --> 08:40.318
I need to see Jackie.

08:41.622 --> 08:42.821
There's no Jackie here.

08:43.724 --> 08:45.924
Go get my daughter now,
you idiot.

08:47.628 --> 08:49.060
Listen, bitch.

08:49.162 --> 08:50.462
There's no Jackie here.

08:55.202 --> 08:57.802
Ever wonder
what 50,000 volts
feels like?

08:58.739 --> 08:59.604
Pretty please.

09:01.041 --> 09:02.407
Go get Jackie now.

09:03.744 --> 09:04.609
Jack.

09:11.318 --> 09:12.951
What [muted] do you want?

09:13.520 --> 09:14.619
I wanna help you.

09:15.122 --> 09:16.421
It's a bit late now.

09:16.523 --> 09:19.457
I'm working on something
that could change your life.

09:20.260 --> 09:22.060
Can we go somewhere
private and talk?

09:26.934 --> 09:28.934
I have nothing more
to say to you.

09:31.738 --> 09:34.606
Will you at least take this,
for protection?

09:34.608 --> 09:38.209
The only thing that I need
protection from is you.

09:51.858 --> 09:53.124
[Max] All right, guys!

09:53.259 --> 09:55.560
It's five minutes.
Let's, uh, let's wrap it up.

09:55.662 --> 09:57.562
I'm locking up. You guys good?

09:57.664 --> 09:58.964
All right, uh...

09:59.066 --> 10:01.199
Ladies, have a good night.

10:01.702 --> 10:02.701
See you tomorrow.

10:05.005 --> 10:06.204
-Good night.
-Good night.

10:09.042 --> 10:09.908
Good night.

10:10.510 --> 10:12.644
See ya. Hey, you.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.446
Great work today, really.

10:14.481 --> 10:15.547
Really loved it.

10:17.317 --> 10:19.117
Aw, come on, guys.

10:19.219 --> 10:20.384
[groans] All right, okay.

10:20.386 --> 10:22.153
Two minutes, all right?
Then we gotta head out.

10:27.227 --> 10:28.293
Hey, Margot.

10:28.295 --> 10:29.828
Just, uh, two minutes.
I'm just locking up.

10:30.530 --> 10:31.363
Two.

10:41.341 --> 10:42.507
[exhales]

10:44.044 --> 10:46.811
[sighing]

10:49.950 --> 10:50.815
[sighs]

10:53.353 --> 10:54.419
Everybody gone?

10:54.421 --> 10:55.687
Yeah.

10:55.689 --> 10:57.055
[lock clicks]

10:57.157 --> 10:59.057
So, I've been
thinking about it,

10:59.125 --> 11:02.560
and I have a theory
why we're losing our audience.

11:02.662 --> 11:06.564
I think we need to change
the types of victims
that we cast.

11:06.633 --> 11:08.600
I know you've been
against it in the past,

11:08.702 --> 11:11.336
but I think we need
to try a woman.

11:11.438 --> 11:12.604
I brought you some options.

11:12.706 --> 11:15.206
Now, they're all great,
all of them believable.

11:15.208 --> 11:17.142
But, Amber, here...

11:17.911 --> 11:19.144
I think she'd be a great fit.

11:19.212 --> 11:20.712
[knocking at door]

11:31.858 --> 11:33.425
[knocking quickens]

11:34.361 --> 11:36.027
I thought you said
everyone was gone.

11:36.730 --> 11:37.829
Yeah, I did.

11:39.633 --> 11:40.932
Who's there?

11:42.602 --> 11:43.435
[door crashes open]

11:44.037 --> 11:44.903
Good evening.

11:46.606 --> 11:48.640
Oh, please, take a seat.

11:49.743 --> 11:51.009
[breath trembling]

11:51.845 --> 11:52.711
Sit down.

11:58.218 --> 11:59.150
[whispers] Sit.

12:03.156 --> 12:05.724
It's such an honor
to finally meet you...

12:08.528 --> 12:09.527
...Majesty.

12:12.632 --> 12:14.132
Oh, I'm a big fan.

12:15.302 --> 12:18.236
All that Bitcoin
I put into your pocket...

12:18.338 --> 12:20.505
Well, now, I want it back.

12:23.810 --> 12:25.510
What the hell
are you talking about?

12:26.813 --> 12:28.513
This whole operation
is [muted].

12:29.483 --> 12:32.050
Now, what would happen

12:32.119 --> 12:34.719
if your loyal viewers
found out?

12:39.059 --> 12:40.125
I want my money back...

12:42.129 --> 12:43.661
...with interest.

12:45.332 --> 12:46.531
[inhales] So...

12:47.400 --> 12:50.235
How much of that
beautiful Bitcoin

12:50.336 --> 12:53.037
has this freakshow
earned so far?

12:58.745 --> 13:00.111
[breath trembling]

13:00.246 --> 13:01.312
[mimicking Max]

13:02.516 --> 13:03.414
Uh...

13:04.518 --> 13:05.517
[Alex] Hmm?

13:05.619 --> 13:06.751
[chuckles softly]

13:07.554 --> 13:08.853
-[gunshot]
-[groans]

13:08.955 --> 13:11.723
[yelps and groans]

13:11.725 --> 13:14.159
-[grunting]
-How much, <i> pendejo?</i>

13:14.260 --> 13:15.260
I don't know.

13:15.328 --> 13:16.961
[panting]

13:17.063 --> 13:18.262
I'm just a hired hand.

13:18.331 --> 13:20.064
I don't, I don't know
about the business. Please...

13:20.133 --> 13:22.433
Oh, so, you're the boss?

13:23.236 --> 13:24.402
What the hell
do I need you for?

13:26.139 --> 13:27.806
-No, no! [grunts]
-[gunshots]

13:31.411 --> 13:32.343
[sighs]

13:35.348 --> 13:36.214
So...

13:37.517 --> 13:38.416
...boss.

13:41.621 --> 13:42.620
What's it gonna be?

13:45.158 --> 13:47.225
If you kill me,
you get [muted].

13:47.828 --> 13:49.327
[clicks tongue] True.

13:51.331 --> 13:54.232
But, what if I killed
your daughter, instead?

13:56.403 --> 13:59.204
-[sobs]
-Uh-uh-uh-uh.

13:59.306 --> 14:01.639
I just want the Bitcoin.

14:01.741 --> 14:05.343
Now be a good mommy,
and little Jackie gets
to live another day.

14:05.412 --> 14:07.412
Prove to me she's not hurt.

14:18.558 --> 14:20.859
[crowd cheering]

14:20.994 --> 14:22.827
[cell phone vibrating]

14:27.400 --> 14:28.465
Yeah?

14:28.535 --> 14:29.734
[Alex on phone] <i> Let me</i>
<i> see the girl.</i>

14:29.803 --> 14:31.135
[soft whimpering]

14:35.809 --> 14:36.641
Okay.

14:37.944 --> 14:40.411
[Jackie shuddering]

14:41.815 --> 14:43.047
[crying]

14:44.985 --> 14:46.050
[gasps]

14:55.228 --> 14:56.427
It's not here.

14:57.397 --> 14:58.763
It's at home.

15:00.133 --> 15:01.032
Shall we?

15:01.434 --> 15:02.500
[Alex sighs]

15:03.637 --> 15:04.502
Come on.

15:29.129 --> 15:30.328
[Margot whispers] It's okay.

15:38.705 --> 15:40.405
It's okay. It's okay.

15:40.407 --> 15:41.639
-[dog whines]
-Stay.

16:07.033 --> 16:09.100
[Alex] Now this is a wallet.

16:09.936 --> 16:11.502
Your recovery phrase, please.

16:24.217 --> 16:25.550
They are behind the picture.

16:37.630 --> 16:38.730
[glass shatters]

16:51.945 --> 16:53.444
[Alex] Give me the passcode.

16:53.546 --> 16:54.545
Hey!

16:58.952 --> 17:00.018
Margot.

17:01.521 --> 17:03.321
Open the door.

17:04.524 --> 17:05.723
You're gonna let
your daughter die

17:05.725 --> 17:08.159
because of some
stupid Bitcoin?

17:08.228 --> 17:10.128
-[dog whines]
-I will do it.

17:15.035 --> 17:16.034
I'm doing it.

17:18.705 --> 17:19.604
[lock clicks]

17:23.510 --> 17:25.943
[clicking]

17:50.303 --> 17:51.402
[dog whimpers softly]

18:01.414 --> 18:03.214
-[dog barks]
-[gasps]

18:03.950 --> 18:05.750
[barking]

18:05.852 --> 18:07.218
[whispers] Listen.

18:07.220 --> 18:08.719
[cries] Don't hurt
my daughter.

18:08.822 --> 18:10.621
Give me the [muted]
code, Margot.

18:10.623 --> 18:11.956
[dog barking]

18:12.024 --> 18:14.959
-Give me the [muted]
code, Margot!
-[dog barking]

18:15.061 --> 18:17.261
-I'm gonna shoot
the [muted] dog.
-[cries] Put the gun down.

18:17.363 --> 18:19.230
Give me the [muted]
code, Margot!

18:19.365 --> 18:20.965
-[taser fires]
-[electricity crackling]

18:21.033 --> 18:23.201
[dog barking]

18:29.609 --> 18:30.808
-[Margot shrieks]
-[dog barks]

18:44.924 --> 18:46.457
[panting]

18:46.559 --> 18:48.759
[in distorted voice] <i> Time's</i>
<i> almost up, my friends.</i>

18:48.828 --> 18:50.528
<i> 30 seconds left.</i>

18:51.131 --> 18:53.164
<i> Highest tip wins.</i>

18:53.232 --> 18:55.099
<i> Choose your weapon.</i>

18:55.201 --> 18:57.235
<i> Which one is it going to be</i>

18:57.270 --> 18:58.936
<i> Time's starting to run out.</i>

18:59.005 --> 19:01.205
-[Alex struggling]
<i> -Majesty wants to play.</i>

19:02.041 --> 19:03.241
[stifled scream]

19:03.309 --> 19:05.743
-[Alex straining]
<i> -Oh, we have a winner.</i>

19:05.812 --> 19:07.145
[wailing]

19:07.246 --> 19:09.413
<i> Great choice.</i>

19:10.316 --> 19:12.350
[struggling]

19:21.928 --> 19:24.228
[Alex cries]

19:27.800 --> 19:30.234
[exclaiming in horror]

19:31.204 --> 19:33.938
[stifled screaming]

19:34.040 --> 19:35.139
[muffled] Margot, no!

19:35.208 --> 19:37.108
No, no, no!

19:40.547 --> 19:42.613
[wailing]

19:44.250 --> 19:46.050
[panting]

19:57.330 --> 19:58.262
[screams]

20:03.203 --> 20:05.236
[gasping and coughing]

20:05.338 --> 20:06.504
Margot, don't do it.

20:06.573 --> 20:09.840
You're not a killer,
Margot. [yelping]

20:09.943 --> 20:12.043
-[in normal voice]
Who the [muted] are you?
-[straining] Margot...

20:12.144 --> 20:14.312
It was your partner!

20:14.414 --> 20:15.813
His idea, not mine.

20:15.915 --> 20:17.048
It was not my idea!

20:17.116 --> 20:18.416
[cries] It was Max's.

20:18.551 --> 20:20.518
It was his stupid
[muted] idea.

20:20.620 --> 20:23.087
[screams]

20:23.089 --> 20:25.523
Go look in your office.
He's not there!

20:25.525 --> 20:27.425
Go see for yourself.
He's not dead!

20:29.529 --> 20:30.428
[coughs and gags]

20:30.563 --> 20:32.129
Margot, please.

20:32.131 --> 20:34.432
[muffled screaming]

20:37.637 --> 20:39.203
[gasps] Oh.

20:39.205 --> 20:42.240
You... [breathing heavily]

20:45.011 --> 20:46.110
A squib.

20:56.723 --> 20:59.223
[Alex grunting]

21:06.332 --> 21:09.033
Oh. No, no, no, no.

21:09.135 --> 21:11.969
No, no. Please.
Please don't. No!

21:11.971 --> 21:14.038
Please don't. Please.

21:14.107 --> 21:17.708
[Margot] Where, exactly,
is my daughter?

21:17.810 --> 21:20.044
She's at Prestige
Dry Cleaners.

21:20.113 --> 21:22.546
It's a dry cleaner's shop
at King and Pine.

21:22.615 --> 21:24.548
She's safe. She's there.

21:24.617 --> 21:26.217
[Margot] How many
people are there?

21:26.219 --> 21:28.919
-[Alex] Just one--
-[Margot] How many
people are there?

21:28.921 --> 21:30.421
Just-- Just two people.

21:30.523 --> 21:32.957
Just two people.
Your partner and my guy.

21:33.025 --> 21:34.225
Max and my guy.

21:34.227 --> 21:35.960
Look, please, you don't
have to do this. Please don't.

21:36.062 --> 21:38.262
Please don't.
We're not killers, Margot.

21:38.364 --> 21:40.164
Don't do this, please.
It's just two guys.

21:40.233 --> 21:41.799
-[Margot] Awe... Ah!
-[Alex] She's safe.
She's safe, no--

21:41.901 --> 21:44.602
[screaming in pain]

21:53.313 --> 21:56.147
[Alex continues groaning]

22:02.822 --> 22:04.355
[chat notifications beeping]

22:10.129 --> 22:11.028
[gags]

22:20.707 --> 22:22.239
[notifications continue]

22:48.501 --> 22:49.800
Oh, my God.

23:01.047 --> 23:02.713
[knocking on door]

23:08.454 --> 23:10.321
[knocking continues]

23:21.601 --> 23:22.600
Where's Alex?

23:25.705 --> 23:26.937
Well, have you heard from him?

23:28.508 --> 23:29.640
[sighs]

23:45.258 --> 23:46.457
[sighs]

23:51.831 --> 23:54.231
We should have
heard from him by now.

23:54.333 --> 23:57.301
-You message him?
-Just chill the [muted]
out, man.

23:57.937 --> 23:59.336
All right?

23:59.438 --> 24:01.505
Your energy is, like,
weirding me out.

24:02.642 --> 24:04.241
Just, eat something.

24:04.343 --> 24:07.845
Could you just try
to contact him, please?

24:07.980 --> 24:08.846
[groans]

24:11.217 --> 24:12.750
It's...

24:12.819 --> 24:14.552
You know, if we don't
get that wallet

24:14.653 --> 24:16.320
that all this
is for nothing, right?

24:16.322 --> 24:17.855
-You get that?
-Just chill.

24:17.990 --> 24:19.957
All right? I'm texting him.

24:23.329 --> 24:25.062
<i> Hey, guys. It's Crypto Stev</i>
<i> bringing you guys</i>

24:25.130 --> 24:27.064
<i> the latest</i>
<i> cryptocurrency tutorials.</i>

24:27.166 --> 24:28.699
<i> In the last tutorial,</i>
<i> I showed you how</i>

24:28.801 --> 24:30.401
<i> you can connect your</i>
<i> cryptocurrency wallet</i>

24:30.403 --> 24:31.735
